BT /F1 14 Tf 72 676 Td (Abstract) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 654 Td (We survey recent advances in attention mechanisms applied to sparse retrieval.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 635 Td (Our analysis covers 78 papers published between 2019 and 2024 and identifies) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 616 Td (three families of approaches. We further propose a unified evaluation protocol.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 597 Td (Keywords: attention, sparse retrieval, survey, information retrieval) Tj ET
BT /F1 14 Tf 72 578 Td (1. Introduction) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 556 Td (Attention mechanisms have transformed the field of information retrieval since) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 537 Td (their introduction. In this paper we systematically review the literature and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 518 Td (categorise existing approaches by their architectural assumptions.) Tj ET
endstream
