BT /F1 14 Tf 72 740 Td (2. Methodology) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 718 Td (We followed the PRISMA guidelines for systematic reviews. Papers were selected) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 699 Td (from ACL, SIGIR, NeurIPS and ICLR proceedings using the query terms described) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 680 Td (in Appendix A. Two annotators independently screened each abstract.) Tj ET
BT /F1 14 Tf 72 661 Td (3. Results) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 639 Td (Table 1 summarises the surveyed approaches. The majority of methods \(61%\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 72 620 Td (rely on learned sparse representations, while 24% use hybrid dense-sparse.) Tj ET
endstream
